text: Nathan de Medina (born 8 October 1997) is a Belgian professional footballer who plays as a defender for Serbian club FK Partizan. ==Club career== De Medina joined Anderlecht in 2004. He made his first team debut on 19 May 2016 in a 5â€“2 away loss to Genk playing the entire match. De Medina signed with Arminia Bielefeld on a free transfer from Royal Excel Mouscron in July 2020, having agreed a three-year contract. He moved to Eintracht Braunschweig in 2022 and to Partizan in 2023. ==Personal life== De Medina was born in Belgium and is of Cape Verdean descent. ==References== ==Other websites== * * * Belgium profile at Belgian FA Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Association football defenders Category:Belgian footballers
